info.description: ## About GoLogin API You can connect to the GoLogin API to integrate it with other programs, enabling process automation using custom scripts and bots. > Note: Using the API requires programming skills. --- ## Supported GoLogin API Packages ### Node.js (Supports Puppeteer) - NPM Package: [GoLogin on npm](https://www.npmjs.com/package/gologin) - Repository: [GitHub - gologinapp/gologin](https://github.com/gologinapp/gologin) - Documentation: [Gologin Docs](https://docs.gologin.com/) --- ### Python (Supports Pyppeteer and Selenium) - Pip Package: [GoLogin on pip](https://pypi.org/project/gologin/) - Repository: [GitHub - gologinapp/pygologin](https://github.com/gologinapp/pygologin) --- ## Rate Limits | Plan | Requests per minute | | --- | --- | | Free & Trial | 300 | | Paid | 1200 | --- # Quickstart Guide ## 1\. Authentication Get your API token: 1. Open the [GoLogin web](https://app.gologin.com/personalArea/TokenApi) or [desktop app](https://gologin.com/download) 2. Settings â†’ API Documentation 3. Click `New Token` to generate your API token. --- ## 2\. Create a Profile Use the [Create Quick Profile](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/21126834/Uz5GnvaL#5dc58d04-2b4b-4f6e-95b0-365720dcff16) request to create a reliable profile. ### 2.1 Update Created Profile (Optional) Use the [Update Profile](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/21126834/Uz5GnvaL#a9cd77e5-ab84-4ea5-ad5c-d68bad21ce87) request to update profile parameters in case you need to change them. --- ## 3\. Set a Proxy Set a proxy to your profile using the [Set profile proxy](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/21126834/Uz5GnvaL#3ebacb64-4356-4d06-b671-a9e6ca80140a) request. --- ## 4\. Run the Profile ### Python Example 1. [Download the example script](https://github.com/gologinapp/pygologin/blob/main/examples/selenium/gologin-selenium.py) 2. `pip3 install gologin selenium` 3. Run the script with your `Profile ID` and `API token`. --- ### JavaScript Example 1. [Download the example script](https://docs.gologin.com/quickstart) 2. `npm install gologin` 3. Run the script with your `Profile ID` and `API token`. > If no `Profile ID` is provided, a new profile is created automatically. --- ## Need help? Reach out to the support team at [https://gologin.com/contact](https://gologin.com/contact/)

request.description: Retrieves detailed information about a specific profile using its ID.

response.name: Retrieve profile

request.description:
This section outlines how to create a profile using the API, including required and optional parameters for optimal reliability and uniqueness.

### Important Notes

- **Required parameters** are necessary to create a profile.
    
- For maximum stability, leave **optional parameters** set to their **default values**, unless customization is needed.
    
- Allowed values can be found in the request body.

### Required Parameters

These parameters are mandatory for creating a valid browser profile.

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `os` | Operating system |

### Optional Parameters

These parameters are optional and come with default values. Modify only if customization is needed.

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `osSpec` | Specific OS/hardware version. |
| `name` | Custom name for the profile. |
| `proxy` | Proxy configuration for the profile. |
| `navigator` | Navigator fingerprint settings. |
| `fonts` | Font fingerprint settings. |
| `webGLMetadata` | Metadata related to WebGL. |
| `webglParams` | Specific WebGL parameters. |
| `notes` | Additional notes related to the profile. |
| `startUrl` | URL to open automatically on profile start. |
| `googleServicesEnabled` | Enables or disables Google services. |
| `lockEnabled` | Enables profile locking. |
| `storage` | Storage settings (local/session). |
| `dns` | Custom DNS server settings. |
| `plugins` | Plugin fingerprint settings. |
| `timezone` | Timezone settings. |
| `audioContext` | AudioContext fingerprint settings. |
| `canvas` | Canvas fingerprint settings. |
| `mediaDevices` | Media device fingerprint configuration. |
| `webRTC` | WebRTC fingerprint settings. |
| `webGL` | WebGL fingerprint settings. |
| `clientRects` | ClientRects fingerprint settings. |
| `chromeExtensions` | List of Chrome extensions to load. |

This section outlines how to create a quick profile using the API, including required and optional parameters for optimal reliability and uniqueness.

Created profile is reliable by default.

### Required Parameters

These parameters are mandatory for creating a valid browser profile.

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `os` | Operating system |
| `name` | Profile name |

### Optional Parameters

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `osSpec` | Specifies hardware/OS version |
| `isM1` | Indicates Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3/M4) compatibility |
| `folderName` | The actual folder name |
| `resolution` | Resolution in x format |

This section outlines how to create a profile using the API, including required and optional parameters for optimal reliability and uniqueness.

### Important Notes

- **Required parameters** are necessary to create a profile. However, they alone do **not guarantee uniqueness**.
    
- For a **unique and reliable profile**, it is recommended to use parameter values obtained from a **"Get New Fingerprint"** request.
    
- For maximum stability, leave **optional parameters** set to their **default values**, unless customization is needed.
    

### Required Parameters

These parameters are mandatory for creating a valid browser profile.

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
